 Port Elizabeth - The Pink Ladies, an independent group of volunteers, who assist in finding missing persons, has appealed to the public for help with locating a missing person from Kwadwesi, Samuel Moloto Matlakala. Samuel Moloto Matlakala (39 years) was reported missing on the 25th of May 2019. According to the Pink Ladies, the last time his wife spoke to him was at 11h00 on the Saturday morning. "He was moving rooms. After that no one spoke to him again." The Pink Ladies said that the vehicle a White Hilux Bakkie JGK 773EC was found burned out in Uitenhage. "It is unknown what he was wearing at the time. If you have information contact Saps Kwadwesi EC Ph: 041-405 4712/041-405 4707/Pink Ladies Org 072 214 7439/083 378 4882/08600 10111." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 